class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

In this solution, we first check if the input number is less than 1. If it is, we return false because powers of three are always positive. Then we calculate the logarithm of the input number with base 3. If the result is an integer (i.e., the remainder when divided by 1 is 0), then the number is a power of three. Otherwise, it's not.

